Context:
The current plugin_list_tabs handler at plugin-list-tabs.ts:29-70 calls `getMergedTabMapping(state)` which merges tabs from all connections into a single `Map<string, TabMapping>`. The `TabMapping` contains `tabs: PluginTabInfo[]` where `PluginTabInfo` is `{ tabId, url, title, ready }` — no connectionId.

getMergedTabMapping at state.ts:467-484:
```typescript
export const getMergedTabMapping = (state: ServerState): Map<string, TabMapping> => {
  const merged = new Map<string, TabMapping>();
  for (const conn of state.extensionConnections.values()) {
    for (const [pluginName, mapping] of conn.tabMapping) {
      const existing = merged.get(pluginName);
      if (existing) {
        const mergedTabs = [...existing.tabs, ...mapping.tabs];
        const bestState = pickBestTabState(existing.state, mapping.state);
        merged.set(pluginName, { state: bestState, tabs: mergedTabs });
      } else {
        merged.set(pluginName, { state: mapping.state, tabs: [...mapping.tabs] });
      }
    }
  }
  return merged;
};
```

Option A: Modify getMergedTabMapping to return tabs with connectionId annotations.
Option B: Don't change getMergedTabMapping (it's used by buildConfigStatePayload for the side panel too), and annotate in plugin_list_tabs directly.

Best approach: Option B — annotate in plugin_list_tabs handler directly by iterating connections:

Changes:
1. Rewrite plugin_list_tabs handler to iterate connections and annotate tabs:
```typescript
handler: (_args, state) => {
  const { plugin } = _args;
  // Build merged tab mapping with connectionId annotations
  const annotatedTabs = new Map<string, { state: TabState; tabs: Array<PluginTabInfo & { connectionId: string }> }>();
  for (const conn of state.extensionConnections.values()) {
    for (const [pluginName, mapping] of conn.tabMapping) {
      const existing = annotatedTabs.get(pluginName);
      const withConn = mapping.tabs.map(t => ({ ...t, connectionId: conn.connectionId }));
      if (existing) {
        existing.tabs.push(...withConn);
        existing.state = pickBestTabState(existing.state, mapping.state);
      } else {
        annotatedTabs.set(pluginName, { state: mapping.state, tabs: withConn });
      }
    }
  }
  // ... then use annotatedTabs instead of getMergedTabMapping for the response
};
```

2. Import `pickBestTabState` from state.ts (it may need to be exported if not already).

Constraints:
- Do NOT change the PluginTabInfo type in shared/ — the connectionId annotation is server-side only for the MCP response. The PluginTabInfo type flows through the extension protocol and doesn't need connectionId.
- Do NOT change getMergedTabMapping — it's used by buildConfigStatePayload (extension-handlers.ts) for the side panel, which doesn't need connectionId annotations.
- The result shape changes from `{ tabId, url, title, ready }` to `{ tabId, url, title, ready, connectionId }` — this is a backwards-compatible addition.

